        <tr><td><strong>Known Dispensary</strong></td><td>Blue Sky Medical (361 Wilton Rd), Blue Sky Rec (104 Fairbanks Rd)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Vertical Integration</strong></td><td>Yes — cultivation, extraction, retail all in Farmington</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Population</strong></td><td>~7,700 (2020 Census)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>County</strong></td><td>Franklin County</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>Farmington is the largest town in Franklin County and home to the University of Maine at Farmington. Despite a modest population of ~7,700, the town is served by Blue Sky Maine — one of Maine's most vertically integrated cannabis operators. Blue Sky runs two separate storefronts in Farmington: a medical dispensary at 361 Wilton Rd and a recreational storefront at 104 Fairbanks Rd. Their operation extends beyond retail to include cultivation, a C1D1 certified extraction facility, and proprietary product development — rare depth for a small-town market.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Blue Sky Maine — Medical Store</h2>
    <p><strong>Address:</strong> 361 Wilton Rd, Farmington, ME 04938<br>
    <strong>Phone:</strong> (207) 778-0726<br>
    <strong>Hours:</strong> Mon-Sat 9am-7pm, Sun 9am-6pm<br>
    <strong>Type:</strong> Medical (Maine medical card required)</p>
    <p>Blue Sky's medical storefront serves the central Maine patient community with flower, concentrates, cartridges, and distillate. Their C1D1 certified extraction facility processes live resin, shatter, batter, and diamonds — products typically found only in larger metro markets. They also offer cultivation services for Maine caregivers and accept out-of-state medical cards from over 30 states.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Blue Sky Maine — Recreational Store</h2>
    <p><strong>Address:</strong> 104 Fairbanks Rd, Farmington, ME 04938<br>
    <strong>Phone:</strong> (207) 578-7328<br>
    <strong>Hours:</strong> Mon-Thu 9am-7pm, Fri-Sat 9am-9pm, Sun 9am-6pm<br>
    <strong>Type:</strong> Recreational (21+)</p>
    <p>The recreational storefront carries Blue Sky's full product line, including MOFGA-certified organic flower grown in living soil on-site in Farmington. Their proprietary processing produces live resin, shatter, batter, diamonds, and cart cartridges. Late hours on Fridays and Saturdays (until 9pm) serve the university student population and weekend traffic.</p>
  </section>

  <Callout title="Vertical Integration" type="passion">
    Blue Sky Maine's full-stack model is distinctive for central Maine. They grow their own flower (MOFGA organic certified), process it in their own extraction lab, and sell directly through their two Farmington storefronts. This eliminates middleman costs and ensures quality control from seed to sale — a competitive advantage in a market that is otherwise served by distributors and wholesalers.
  </Callout>

  <section>
    <h2>Farmington's Market Position</h2>
    <p>Farmington sits roughly equidistant from the Lakes Region (Bridgton, ~25 mi), Auburn-Lewiston (~35 mi), and Waterville (~25 mi). For residents in the intervening communities — Industry, New Sharon, New Vineyard, Jay, Wilton — Farmington is the most convenient dispensary option. Blue Sky's two storefronts mean both medical patients and recreational 21+ customers have dedicated experiences without sharing a single counter space.</p>
    <p>The University of Maine at Farmington provides a consistent customer base, particularly for the recreational storefront. Blue Sky's MOFGA organic certification also appeals to the region's agricultural consumers who value sustainable growing practices.</p>
  </section>

